<jx:comment>
Overall Report Header (conceptual - would be formatted in Excel cells)
Report: Account Activity Detail
Overall Report Period: ${reportStartDate} to ${reportEndDate}
Report Generated: ${reportDate}
</jx:comment>

<jx:forEach items="${accountsDetail}" var="accountData" lastCell="F1"> <jx:comment>Adjust lastCell based on actual Excel layout below this loop for multiple accounts</jx:comment>
Account Name: ${accountData.accountName}
Account Number: ${accountData.accountNumber}

Opening Balance: ${accountData.openingBalance} #[#,##0.00]

| Date       | Transaction ID | Description          | Debit      | Credit     | Running Balance |
<jx:forEach items="${accountData.entries}" var="entry" lastCell="F9"> <jx:comment>Assuming the table starts around row 8-9 and is 6 columns wide (A-F). Adjust lastCell based on actual Excel layout.</jx:comment>
| ${entry.date} | ${entry.transactionId} | ${entry.description} | ${entry.debit} #[#,##0.00] | ${entry.credit} #[#,##0.00] | ${entry.runningBalance} #[#,##0.00] |
</jx:forEach>

Closing Balance: ${accountData.closingBalance} #[#,##0.00]

---------------------------------------------------- <jx:comment> This is a visual separator for the text version. In Excel, use borders or spacing. </jx:comment>
</jx:forEach>
<jx:comment> End of JXLS processing instructions. Any content below the main forEach loop would appear once at the end of the report. </jx:comment>
